<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Holland host Italy in their second matchday clash in the UEFA Nations League tonight.</p>

<p>The Dutch side beat Poland in their opening game with Tottenham's Steven Bergwijn scoring the only goal whilst their rivals were able to grab a draw after Stefano Sensi cancelled out Bosnia's Edin Dzeko goal for a 1-1 draw.</p>

<p>Elsewhere, Scotland travel to Czech Republic in a search for their first victory of the competition, following the frustrating 1-1 draw with Israel in their opener.</p>

<p>Northern Ireland welcome Norway in League B clash after gaining a point in their first game following  a draw with Romania as Erling Haaland and Co look to register their first points of the tournament.</p>

<p>Sportsmail's IEUAN IVETT will provide live Nations League coverage including score, lineups and updates, with full commentary of Holland vs Italy. </p>

